ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.
M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported
e.g., Baseline, 6-Month Follow Up, Year 2; Morning, At Bedtime

ElementDescription: Current issues I am facing could be the first signs of a mental illness
Notes: 1 = Do not agree at all; 2 = Do not agree; 3 = Undecided; 4 = Agree; 5 = Agree completely

ElementDescription: The thought of myself having a mental illness seems doubtful to me
Notes: 1 = Do not agree at all; 2 = Do not agree; 3 = Undecided; 4 = Agree; 5 = Agree completely

ElementDescription: I could be the type of person that is likely to have a mental illness
Notes: 1 = Do not agree at all; 2 = Do not agree; 3 = Undecided; 4 = Agree; 5 = Agree completely

ElementDescription: I see myself as a person that is mentally healthy and emotionally stable
Notes: 1 = Do not agree at all; 2 = Do not agree; 3 = Undecided; 4 = Agree; 5 = Agree completely

ElementDescription: I am mentally stable, I do not have a mental health problem
Notes: 1 = Do not agree at all; 2 = Do not agree; 3 = Undecided; 4 = Agree; 5 = Agree completely
r indicates need to reverse score item; sum calculated if there is data for at least 4 of the 5 items
r indicates need to reverse score item; mean calculated if there is data for at least 4 of the 5 items
